Detailed Description

The "callback" from a CollectorOutput, which gives a new data sequence number that can be acknowledged back to the transmitter.

Version:
Id

Member Function Documentation

void com::xacct::CRANE::collector::ProcessDataSeqNoAck::processDataSeqNoAck (  long  newDataSeqNoToAck  )  throws ConnectionIOException, ProtocolMalformedMsgException, ConfigException
 

This method is called when the outputter decides that an acknowledgment should be sent (e.g., it has committed some records to persistent storage). The connection thread can send an ACK back to the transmitter at this point, instead of waiting for a timer.

Parameters:
newDataSeqNoToAck The last data sequence number that should be ACKed.
